# Component standards (layout, naming, variants)

## Module layout

- Each **importable component module** lives in its **own directory** under the correct layer (`components/ui`, `atoms`, `molecules`, `organisms`).
- Add **`index.ts`** that re-exports the **public API** only (components, types, and `*Variants` helpers when applicable).
- If there is **no** variant API, **`index.ts` exports only** what consumers need. Do **not** add an empty `*Variants.ts` file.
- Prefer imports like **`@/components/ui/button`**, **`@/components/atoms/Typography`**, **`@/components/atoms/Image`** (barrel paths), not deep paths into `*.tsx` files.

### `components/ui/<primitive>/`

Reserve **`components/ui/`** for **shadcn (registry)–generated** components and their normalized folder layout. **Custom** primitives (e.g. app-specific `Image` wrappers) belong under **`components/atoms/`** (or higher layers), not `ui/`.

- **`index.ts`** — barrel: e.g. `Button`, `buttonVariants`, related types.
- **`<primitive>.tsx`** — implementation; **lowercase** filename (`button.tsx`, `card.tsx`) for shadcn alignment.
- **`<primitive>Variants.ts`** (camelCase, e.g. `buttonVariants.ts`) — optional; **required** when the module exposes a **`tailwindVariants`** API (`variant` / `size` / etc.). Keep **server-safe** (no `"use client"`).

After **`shadcn` CLI** adds a **flat** file under `components/ui/`, **normalize** into `components/ui/<name>/` with `index.ts`. Avoid leaving both a flat `<name>.tsx` and a `<name>/` folder (resolution conflicts). Do **not** blindly re-run `shadcn add` for a primitive you already maintain as a folder.

### `components/atoms`, `molecules`, `organisms`

- Same **folder + `index.ts`** pattern.
- Main file: **`<Name>/<Name>.tsx`** — **PascalCase** filename matching the default export (`Typography/Typography.tsx`, `Header/Header.tsx`).
- **`tailwindVariants`** live in **`*Variants.ts`** in that folder (e.g. `typographyVariants.ts`), not inlined in the component file.

## File names and exports

- Place UI components under `components/atoms`, `components/molecules`, or `components/organisms`, each in its **own folder** with **`index.ts`** (see above).
- **File name = default export component name**, both **PascalCase** (e.g. `atoms/Button/Button.tsx` exports `Button`, `molecules/Header/Header.tsx` exports `Header`).
- **Exception:** under **`components/ui/<primitive>/`**, the main file may be **lowercase** (e.g. `button/button.tsx`) to match shadcn conventions; variant modules use **camelCase** `*Variants.ts` (e.g. `buttonVariants.ts`).
- Always use **arrow function** components and non-components.

## Variant modules (`tailwindVariants`)

- When a component uses **`tailwindVariants`** for styling API (`variant`, `size`, etc.), define the variant config in a **sibling camelCase `*Variants.ts`** in the same folder (e.g. `button/buttonVariants.ts`, `atoms/Typography/typographyVariants.ts`).
- Keep **`*Variants.ts` server-safe** (no `"use client"`) unless a variant truly depends on client-only modules.
- The **component file** imports variants and composes with **`classNames`** from `@/lib/utils/classNames/classNames`.
- **`components/ui/<primitive>/`** may use **lowercase** main files (`button.tsx`); **atoms/molecules/organisms** use **PascalCase** (`Typography/Typography.tsx`).

## Style helpers (no abbreviations)

- Use **`classNames`** from `@/lib/utils/classNames/classNames` for clsx + tailwind-merge. Do **not** use **`cn`**.
- Use **`tailwindVariants`** as the binding for tailwind-variants: `import { tv as tailwindVariants } from "tailwind-variants"`. Do **not** call **`tv`** directly in source.

## Server vs client

- Keep **`tailwindVariants`** style definitions in **server-safe** modules (no `"use client"`) when they must be used from Server Components (e.g. `components/ui/button/buttonVariants.ts`). Interactive wrappers stay in `"use client"` files.

## Linting

- **Oxlint** does not enforce PascalCase filenames; follow this rule when adding components.
